Date of Birth: January 10, 1862<br/>
Birthplace: Salt Lake City, Utah, USA<br/>
Ordained apostle: April 8, 1900<br/>
Death: February 9, 1941<br/>
<br/>
Born Jan. 10, 1862, at Salt Lake City, Salt Lake Co., Utah, to Abraham Owen Smoot and Anne Kestine Morrison.
Ordained apostle April 8, 1900, by Lorenzo Snow, at age 38; served in the U.S. Senate, 1903-32; died Feb. 9, 1941, at St. Petersburg, Pinellas Co., Florida, at age 79.